easing your mana regeneration rate.  <br>
<br>
The Ear ring has a 15% mana savings on all DD spells.  Nothing else has a 15% savings on nukes.  Nothing can replace it.  Use it anytime you will be casting DD spells.  <br>
<br>
The Bracer has a 25% improved damage.  Get an improved damage I item until you get the bracers spells.  Then use them, use your money for other spots.  The increased damage will result in less casts per kill which is less mana per kill.  Probably more effective that the Ear ring since we nuke so much.    <br>
<br>
The Ring has spell haste.  Wear it all times.  In emergencies, you need that extra time savings to cast more spells.  Since it is an emergency, you can not plan for it, so wear it all the time.   <br>
<br>
The shoulder item has a 30% extended enhancement.  This makes you shield line, phatom armor line, and damage shield lines last up to 30% longer.  Since you nearly always have these spells up, a 30% increase in time means your cast it 30% fewer times which results in less mana spent per cast.  Always have an extended enhancement item on when casting these spells.  You can swap the item when casting these spells, but I cast a damage shield so often, I just leave it in the spot.  Once I get a shoulder FT item, I will have to start swapping.  <br>
<br>
The neck items has a 10% reagant conservation.  I really just swap this item when casting a pet, and only if I think bout.  Most of our spells use cheap gems and the savings is very minor.  <br>
<br>
In addition, I would recommend a Mana Preservation Item.  All spells except Pet summons benefit from this 10% savings.  The black alloy mediallion has level II of this effect and +5 int as well and can be bought for ~ 700pp.  You will be good till your 49th level. This will affect the same spell lines listed in the shoulder item, but will also on all heals and non pet summons.  With a horse and this item, you can summon all your food, water, weapons, pet weapons, vision enhancement, dimensional bags, and pet armor and be nearly full mana when finished instead of medding for 5 minutes.  <br>
<br>
I would also recommend an summoning efficiency item.  The enshrouded veil has summoning efficiency III plus some mana.  It also can be bought ~ 700pp.<br>
<br>
A summoning haste item helps get a new pet off after the old one dies.  The robe of elements is a decent robe of get Brell's Girdle and be set until 65.  <br>
<br>
At different times, I used my heal spell alot.  An improved healing item can really help in these situations.  I used a Book of Obulus in the secondary slot.  It runs about 2000pp and has a nice int bonus as well.  <br>
<br>
But the most important purchase, a Horse.  If you can afford the 100k horse, you will have mana regeneration while casting, no sit agro, and nothing will ever catch you.  If you can't afford that horse, get the low end horse.  You still get the mana regen and the no sit aggro. <br>
<br>
Save some money for KEI.  As a mage, even with a horse, you will always be oom and medding.  KEI will reduce that time drastrically.  With a horse, you may never go OOM and make you a killing machine. <br>
<br>
Another recommendation is to use a 1hb.  The epic and several other great stat weapons are 1hb.  Goto the bazaar and find the lowest delay 1hb weapon you can find and use it.  I used 1h pericing to start.  Then tried 2hb for a while for greater damage.  It became obvious that I would not be able to keep either maxed so I switched back to pericing.  Start with 1hb with a low delay to help keep your offense and 1hb skill maxed.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28>Equipment</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
